{
  "stem": "812.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I-- I couldn't, because there was still an awful lot of heartache and misery surrounding us, and-- and I was in constant pain and couldn't walk.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- but it was enormous gratitude that we survived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I-- despite the fact that my father didn't make it, I do feel that my-- my games of superstition that I-- was such a part of my life in Bergen-Belsen was not in vain.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I do feel that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I won in that game, because my father did see us liberated, and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and I-- I see his presence in our children, in our grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and I have very mixed feelings about all of this, that that has happened-- very mixed feelings.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There-- there are feelings within me of-- of anger.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, there are feelings of gratitude.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Anger because how could something so incredible, something so horrendous have happened?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And how could people do something like this to one another?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Animals don't do this to one another.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How could people, so-called intelligent people, allow this to happen?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And how could this have been allowed to have happened altogether?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Where was the man upstairs?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And yet, I know that people are doing it to themselves.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I am grateful that I survived, healthy in mind and body, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that I have a wonderful, kind, understanding, and generous, loving husband, and that together we were allowed to perpetuate our heritage with a wonderful family.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we have three wonderful children-- David, Susan, and Michael, who are happily married, David to Lisa, Susan to Rob, and Michael to Rachel.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
